            <title>[KAFKA-2618] Disable SSL renegotiation for 0.9.0.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2618</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2609&quot; title=&quot;SSL renegotiation code paths need more tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2609&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2609&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we don&apos;t have enough tests for SSL renegotiation to be confident that it works well. In addition, neither the clients or the server make use of renegotiation at this point.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For 0.9.0.0, we should disable renegotiation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
